President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Todd A. Weiler has been nominated as Assistant Secretary of Defense for Manpower and Reserve Affairs, Nelson Reyneri as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation, Kelly Keiderling as Ambassador to the Oriental Republic of Uruguay, and Stephen Schwartz as Ambassador to the Federal Republic of Somalia. Raymond G. Farmer, Tom McLeary, Mike Rothman, and Heather A. Steinmiller have been nominated as Members of the Board of Directors of the National Association of Registered Agents and Brokers. Additionally, President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Thomas M. Gallas as a Member of the National Capital Planning Commission, Ethel Brooks, Sara Darehshori, and Norman Eisen as Members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.